- Medium confidence on the live explanation for “code-index x3.” The code strongly supports “per-session bridge launchers,” and the diagnosis confirms seven interactive runtimes, but I did not inspect the live process tree or socket clients in this read-only pass.
- I could not recover the exact kill event for the current stale sockets. The diagnosis also states no persistent daemon/launcher log was found for the event at `live-diagnosis.md:10`.
